                  Carroll D. </a>(2007). <i>Essays on Women in Earliest
                  Christianity, Vol. 1</i>. Wipf and Stock Publishers.
                p[p.&nbsp;208-209. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISBN_%28identifier%29"
                  class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&nbsp;<a
                  href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781556355400"
                  title="Special:BookSources/9781556355400"><bdi>9781556355400</bdi></a>.</cite></span></div>
          <div class="rt-content mw-parser-output"><span class="reference-text"><cite
                class="citation book cs1"></cite></span><br>
            <h4>Evidence 8</h4>
            <div class="ds-markdown ds-markdown--block" style="--ds-md-zoom: 1.143;">
              <p>Theologians<a href="https://www.therestorationmovement.com/_states/tennessee/lipscomb,bio.htm">
                  David Lipscomb</a> and <a href="https://digitalcommons.pepperdine.edu/heritage_center/14/">J.
                  W. Shepherd</a>, in their <em>Commentary on 1st Corinthians</em>,
                explain the traditional interpretation of 1 Corinthians 11. They
                write:</p>
              <blockquote>
                <p>"Every man who covers his head while praying or prophesying
                  acknowledges dependence on an earthly head rather than Christ,
                  his heavenly head, dishonoring Him."</p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>They connect this to the Old Testament, where male priests wore
                turbans or caps. Since Jesus was not yet revealed, there was no
                command for men to pray with uncovered heads. The New Testament
                practice reflects the new covenant, where men pray uncovered to
                honor Christ directly. This highlights the shift from Old
                Testament symbolism to New Testament worship.</p>
            </div>
            <p></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p> </p>
    <br>
    <div class="rt-hoverArea">
      <div class="rt-scroll">
        <div class="rt-content mw-parser-output"> <span class="reference-text"><cite
