                </p>
                <h4>Evidence 1<span style="color: #222222;">4</span></h4>
                <blockquote>
                  <p>"<strong>κατακαλύπτω G2877</strong> (katakalyptō): to cover
                    up, to veil;<br>
                    <strong>ἀκατακάλυπτος G184</strong> (akatakalyptos):
                    uncovered."</p>
                </blockquote>
              </div>
              <div class="rt-content mw-parser-output">
                <p>Beetham, Christopher A., ed. (2021). <em>The Concise New
                    International Dictionary of New Testament Theology and
                    Exegesis</em>. Zondervan Academic. ISBN 978-0-310-59848-0. </p>
                <h4>Evidence 1<span style="color: #222222;">5</span></h4>
                <blockquote>
                  <p>I offer this survey of ancient headcovering practices in
                    the hope that it will clear away some common misconceptions,
                    and bring into sharper focus the customs which many biblical
                    expositors have held to be so important for an understanding
                    of the Apostle Paul's instruction to the Corinthians
